                               int startColIdx)
                                    throws org.knime.core.node.InvalidSettingsException
        Checks a column name exists. If not, tries to autoguess, and matches as substring (if non-'null'), and DataType. Starts at supplied column index and works back through the table
        Parameters:
        spec - The input data table spec
        nameFromSettingsModel - The name supplied from the settings model
        type - The type of column
        substringMatch - A substring to match - ignored if null
        startColIdx - The start column index
        Returns:
        The column name - either the validated name from the settings model, or a guessed name of the correct type
